The paper deals with error-correcting codes and their decoding, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of neural networks in the decoding process suggests a possible fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NI) sub-category. The application of the proposed decoding algorithm to 5G mobile communications systems suggests a possible fit for the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of trainable weights in the neural algorithm suggests a possible fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of factor graphs and belief propagation suggests a possible fit for the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
